 of measuring systemic risk and explores alternative approaches. Among the topics discussed are the challenges of tying regulations to specific quantitative measures, the effects of learning and adaptation on the evolution of the market, and the distinction between the shocks that start a crisis and the mechanisms that enable it to grow.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aFinancial riskxMathematical modelsvCongresses. 0aOperational riskvCongresses. 0aRisk assessmentvCongresses. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / General.2bisacsh1 aAcharya, Viral V., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAdrian, Tobias, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrunnermeier, Markus K., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDanielsson, Jon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDe Nicolò, Gianni, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDrehmann, Mathias, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDuffey, Romney B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aElliott, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaubrich, Joseph G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaubrich, Joseph G., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHu, Henry T. C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKapadia, Sujit, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLo, Andrew W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLo, Andrew W., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLucchetta, Marcella, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNguyen, Hoai-Luu Q., econtribu